The paper discusses the protection of user privacy in the context of Web browsing history, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The proposed approach involves manipulating the Web browsing history while retaining its utility, which involves techniques related to information retrieval (cs.IR) and databases (cs.DB). The paper also discusses the potential impact of the approach on personalized online services, which falls under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper addresses the challenge of privacy protection, which is a topic of interest in the field of cyber-physical systems (cs.CY).
